11/05/2006
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- The spokesman for the UN tribunal prosecutors, Anton Nikiforov, said on Wednesday (10 May) that the tribunal has no doubt indictee Ratko Mladic is in Serbia. He refused to comment on recent reports of stepped-up activity by Serbian police and security services, but insisted that the Serbian government must arrest the fugitive and extradite him to The Hague. On Tuesday, police reportedly arrested another suspected Mladic associate, this one a retired member of the Serbia-Montenegro Army.
In other news, police in Republika Srpska detained Bosnian Serb Zivko Miletic, who is accused of committing war crimes in Foca. He was arrested on Wednesday at the order of the Sarajevo Cantonal prosecutors. (Blic, RTS, Nezavisne novine - 11/05/06; Beta, Tanjug, RTRS - 10/05/06)
